theorem
Th59: (((not x in L) & L is  being_line) implies (ex x1 st (ex x2 st (L = ( Line (x1,x2) ) & ( x - x1 ) _|_ ( x2 - x1 )))))
proof
assume that
A1: (not x in L)
and
A2: L is  being_line;
consider y0,y1 such that A3: y0 <> y1 and A4: L = ( Line (y0,y1) ) by A2,EUCLID_4:def 2;
A5: ( y0 - y1 ) <> ( 0* n ) by A3,CKB10:1;
consider x1 being (Element of ( REAL n )) such that A6: x1 in ( Line (y0,y1) ) and A7: ( y0 - y1 ),( x - x1 ) are_orthogonal  by CKB51:1;
( x - x1 ) <> ( 0* n ) by A1,A4,A6,CKB10:1;
then A8: ( y0 - y1 ) _|_ ( x - x1 ) by A7,A5,CKB52:def 1;
take x1;
consider x2 being (Element of ( REAL n )) such that A9: x1 <> x2 and A10: x2 in L by A2,EUCLID_4:14;
take x2;
A11: ( x2 - x1 ) <> ( 0* n ) by A9,CKB10:1;
(ex a being Real st ( x2 - x1 ) = ( a * ( y0 - y1 ) )) by A4,A6,A10,CKB32:1;
then ( x2 - x1 ) // ( y0 - y1 ) by A5,A11,CKB33:def 1;
hence thesis by A2,A4,A6,A8,A9,A10,CKB31:1,CKB53:1;
end;
